class Solution {
    public String longestPalindrome(String s) {
        return longRecur(s,0,s.length()-1);
    }

    String longRecur(String str,int s,int e) 
        if(s==e) return String.valueOf(str.charAt(s)); //base
        if(s>e) return "";

        //case 1
        if(str.charAt(s) == str.charAt(e)) {
            String both = longRecur(str,s+1,e-1);
            if(both.length() ==  e-1-(s+1)+1) //check if the remaining string is also a palindrome
                return str.charAt(s) + both + str.charAt(e);
        }

        //case2
        String left = longRecur(str,s+1,e);
        String right = longRecur(str,s,e-1);
        if(left.length() > right.length()) return left;
        else return right;
    }
}
```

2. recursion + memo =  top-down dp (I'm adding this as requested)
```
class Solution {

    public String longestPalindrome(String s) {
        return longRecur(s,0,s.length()-1, new String[s.length()][s.length()]);
    }

    private String longRecur(String str,int s,int e, String[][] memo) {
        //base
        if(s==e) return String.valueOf(str.charAt(s)); 
        if(s>e) return "";

        if(memo[s][e]!=null) return memo[s][e];

        //case 1
        if(str.charAt(s) == str.charAt(e)) {
            String both = longRecur(str,s+1,e-1,memo);
            if(both.length() ==  e-1-(s+1)+1) { //check if the remaining string is also a palindrome
                String ret = str.charAt(s) + both + str.charAt(e);
                memo[s][e] = ret;
                return ret;
            }
        }

        //case2
        String left = longRecur(str,s+1,e,memo);
        String right = longRecur(str,s,e-1,memo);

        if(left.length() > right.length()) {
            memo[s][e] = left;
            return left;
        } else {
            memo[s][e] = right;
            return right;
        }
    }
}
```

there could be a few bottom-up dp variants.



3. dp, using String[][] longestPalindrome
	we can directly store strings into the matrix. 
	it's a direct conversion of the recursion solution above.
	time O(n^2), space O(n^2) 
	but then since it's directly handling strings it's relatively slower than other dp variants below.

```
class Solution {

    public String longestPalindrome(String str) {

        int n = str.length();
        String[][] dp = new String[n][n]; //longestPalindrome

		//init the matrix
        for(int i =0;i<n;i++) 
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++) 
               dp[i][j] ="";

        //base
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) 
            dp[i][i] = String.valueOf(str.charAt(i));

        //fill in the upper right half
        for(int s=n-1; s>=0; s--)  {
            for(int e = s+1; e<n; e++) {
                if(str.charAt(s) == str.charAt(e)) {
                  String both = dp[s+1][e-1];
                    if( both.length() ==  e-1-(s+1)+1) {
                        dp[s][e] = str.charAt(s) + both + str.charAt(e);
                        continue;
                    }
                }

                String left = dp[s+1][e];
                String right = dp[s][e-1];
                if(left.length() > right.length()) dp[s][e] = left;
                else dp[s][e] = right;
            }
        }
        return dp[0][n-1]; 
    }
} 
```

4. dp, using int[][] maxLength (i.e. the length of the longest palindrome)
instead of handling strings directly, we can just keep track of maxLen and return the substring at the end.
time O(n^2), space O(n^2) 

```
class Solution {

    public String longestPalindrome(String str) {

        int n = str.length();
        int[][] dp = new int[n][n]; //means the length of the longest palindrom of str.substring(i,j+1)
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)//base
            dp[i][i] = 1;
        int maxLen=1, maxStart =0;

        for(int s = n-1;s>=0;s--) {
            for(int e=s+1;e<n;e++) {

                if(str.charAt(s) ==str.charAt(e)) {
                    if(dp[s+1][e-1] == e-1 -(s+1)+1) {
                        dp[s][e] = dp[s+1][e-1] +2;
                        int len = e-s+1;
                        if(maxLen<len) {
                            maxLen = len;
                            maxStart = s;
                        } 
                        continue;
                    }
                }

                int left = dp[s+1][e];
                int right = dp[s][e-1];
                dp[s][e] = Math.max(left,right);
            }
        }
        return str.substring(maxStart,maxStart+maxLen);
    }
} 
```


