solutions.content:
# Intuition


# Approach
- for a string s of length greater than 2 to be palindrome there are two conditons:
    1. s[start]=s[end]
    2. substring(start+1,end-1) should also be a palindrome

- for example, string s=ababa
s[start]=a 
s[end]=a
substring from start+1 to end-1 i.e. bab is also palindrome.
So string s is plaindrome.

- Create a 2d vector to store whether from index i to j of string is palindrome or not.
- Here i and j represent start and end index of string respectively.
- Base cases:
substring string of length 1 is always a palindrome so mark dp[i][j]=1 for j-i==0(length 1).
the above condition only work if the length is greater than 2 so also precalculate for substring of length 2 whether it is palindrome or not.
- Now start filling 2d vector column wise for substring of length 3 or more with the two palindrome conditions.Colmum wise because for substring (0,4) one need (1,3) hence column wise.
- Now find the maximum length substring from 2d vector.





# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n^2)

- Space complexity:
O(n^2)
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string longestPalindrome(string s) {
        int n=s.size();
        vector<vector<int>>dp(n,vector<int>(n,0));

        //base case
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
            {
                if((j-i)==0||(j-i)==1)//substr of length 1 or 2
                {
                    if(s[i]==s[j])
                    {
                        dp[i][j]=1;
                    }
                    else
                    {
                        dp[i][j]=0;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        // to be a palindrom conditions
        //s[i]==s[j]
        //substr(i+1,j-1) is also palindrome



        //fill it column wise
        for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
        {
            for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
            {
                if((j-i)>1)//substr of length 2 or more //upper triangle only bcz i <j
                {
                    if(s[i]==s[j]&&dp[i+1][j-1]==1)
                    {
                        dp[i][j]=1;
                    }
                    else
                    {
                        dp[i][j]=0;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        int start=0;
        int maxi=1;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
            {
                if(dp[i][j]==1)
                {
                    if(maxi<=j-i+1)
                    {
                        maxi=j-i+1;
                        start=i;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return s.substr(start,maxi);        
    }
};
```

