### Approach:

The algorithm below is very simple and easy to understand. The idea is to ***fix a center and expand in both directions*** to get longer palindromes and keep track of the start and end position of longest palindrome seen so far.

**Time Complexity :** Outer loop runs for n times and we have two inner loops which run for n times. 
              ` n*(n+n)=>O(n^2)`

**Space Cpmplexity :**  O(1)

***l*** : This points to the left most index of pallindrom string.
***h*** : This points to the right most index of pallindrom string.

***start*** : This points to the starting position of current maximum length pallindromic string.
***end*** : This points to the end position of current maximum length pallindromic string.



```
string longestPalindrome(string s) {
        int start=0;
        int end=0;
        int n=s.size();
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++)
        {

		    // for even length palindroms
            int l=i-1;           
            int h=i;
            while(l>=0 && h<n && s[l]==s[h])   //if both left and right is same then expand the length by of pallindrom by moving l and h accordingly
            {
                if(end-start < h-l )           // if current length of pallindrom is greater than previous the update sart and end accordingly
                {
                    start=l;
                    end=h;
                }
                l--;
                h++;
            }

			//for odd length palindroms
            l=i-1;
            h=i+1;
            while(l>=0 && h<n && s[l]==s[h])
            {
                if(end-start < h-l )
                {
                    start=l;
                    end=h;
                }
                l--;
                h++;
            }
        }

        string ans="";
        for(int i=start;i<=end;i++)
            ans+=s[i];

        return ans;
    }
```

