I didn't find any iterative Morris Traversal solution for this problem in the discussion section, So I am sharing my Java solution which has O(n) time complexity and uses a O(1) extra space. Feel free to discuss anything about the approach in the comments section. Upvote if you find it useful as it would help others to find this post quickly.
#### **Morris Traversal Algorithm**
For understanding morris traversal algorithm and about threaded binary tree, you can go through [**this leetcode article**](https://leetcode.com/problems/binary-tree-inorder-traversal/discuss/148939/CPP-Morris-Traversal), where the author has explained it nicely with figures. 
#### **Time and Space Complexity**
The time complexity is O(n), n is length of preorder array, because each node in the binary tree is visited at most two times. First time as a parent of current node, second time is when we are trying to find the correct parent whose right child is curr (current node). Auxiliary space used in this solution is also O(1) as we are not using stack or recursion or any other data structure.
#### **Commented Code**
```
public TreeNode buildTreeMorris(int[] preorder, int[] inorder){
    var parent = new TreeNode(preorder[0]);
    var root = parent;
    for (int i = 1, j=0; i < preorder.length; i++) {
        var curr = new TreeNode(preorder[i]);
        //checking if we should continue adding nodes to the left of parent node
        if(parent.val != inorder[j]){
            parent.left = curr;
            // creating the thread to inorder successor so that we can return to it when we
            // are done creating its left subtree
            curr.right = parent;
        }else{
            j++;

            //finding the correct parent whose right child is curr (current node)
            while(parent.right != null && parent.right.val == inorder[j]){
                var temp = parent;
                parent = parent.right;
                //removing the thread which is no longer reguired
                temp.right = null;
                j++;
            }
            //creating the correct thread
            curr.right = parent.right;
            //breaking the previous thread and placing the right child in place of it 
            parent.right = curr;
        }
        parent = curr;
    }
    //removing the remaining threads
    while (parent.right != null) {
        var temp = parent.right;
        parent.right = null;
        parent = temp;
    }
    return root;
}
```
For writing the code, I took help from following helpful discussion section posts:
1. [Link 1](https://leetcode.com/problems/construct-binary-search-tree-from-preorder-traversal/discuss/589051/Morris'-algorithm-(O(n)-time-O(n)-space))
2. [Link 2](https://leetcode.com/problems/construct-binary-tree-from-preorder-and-inorder-traversal/discuss/34555/The-iterative-solution-is-easier-than-you-think!/32916/)

