solutions.content:
Follow intuition - 

Preorder first node will be root. 
Order property says anything left of root in array will be left subtree of root and right of root in array will be right subtree.
So, fetch that, find the index of root.
and then recursively calculate your subarrays and place the root
```
class Solution {
    public TreeNode buildTree(int[] preorder, int[] inorder) {
        if(preorder.length == 0) return null; //Our terminating condition
        TreeNode root = new TreeNode(preorder[0]);
        int index = -1;
        for(int i = 0; i < inorder.length; i++){// find the root location in inorder
           if(inorder[i]==root.val){
               index=i;
               break;
           }    
        }
		//all the values to the left are part of left subtree
        int[] leftPre = Arrays.copyOfRange(preorder, 1, index + 1);  // we need this to process our root everytime we segregate and make a recursive call
        int[] rightPre = Arrays.copyOfRange(preorder, index + 1, preorder.length); 
        int[] leftIn = Arrays.copyOfRange(inorder, 0, index + 1); //find the left subtree
        int[] rightIn = Arrays.copyOfRange(inorder, index + 1, inorder.length);//find the left subtree
        root.left=buildTree(leftPre, leftIn); //build the left subtree
        root.right=buildTree(rightPre,rightIn); // build the right subtree

        return root;
    }
}
```


