pretty print Java and a few hints

here is a few hints on what I did - I have not looked at other solutions but this is just a few lines of code and runs in 97% of so performance rankings.  It took me a lot of thinking about and head scratching.

1. a lookup map on both arrays is useful i.e. node value to position in array.
2. recursion is a natural choice where if we have a construct function taking above maps the root value for the given sub tree, the preorder array and bounds of the sub tree (initially 0 and preorder.length - 1.  left is a call to this recursive function on left bound tree to left of the root and right similar.
3. if (start >= end) we have no subtree so create return a node with that value at current root and return left, right are null in this case.
4. get 2 indices lookup the above maps we will call them inOrderIndex and preOrderIndex.
5. looking at the preorder array our left root in next recursive call is always next in preorder list i.e. we call outr recursive function with preorder[preOrderIndex + 1]
6. on right the root is preorder[preOrderIndex + nodesOnLeft + 1]
7. nodesOnLeft = inOrderIndex - start;
8. nodesOnRight = end - inOrderIndex;
9. on left recurive call start, end are inOrderIndex - nodesOnLeft, inOrderIndex - 1
10 on right recursive call inOrderIndex + 1, inOrderIndex + nodesOnRight)



